## R code repository for two species co-expression network analysis for Medicago-Sinorhizobia symbiosis

## This repository accompanies the manuscripts: 
## Byungwook Choi, Peter Tiffin
## Department of Plant and Microbial Biology, University of Minnesota


## This repository contains R scripts and processes datasets used to analyze host-symbiont co-expression networks in the Medicago-Sinorhizoba symbiosis using dual RNA-seq transcriptome data.

## The analyses include:
DataProcessing
- Preprocessing of dual-seq expression data
- generation of expression profiles such as TPM/codinglength, TPM, and Log2(TPM+1) values.
Co-expression networks using WGCNA (in "WGCNA")
- construction of co-expression networks
- module detection and hub gene identification
GO enrichment analysis (in "GOEnrichmentAnalysis")
- functional enrichment of module genes and highly correlated interspecies genes
Comparison of co-expression networks across different networks (in "NetworkComparison")
- comparison betweeen S+M, S-only, and S+M, M-only networks
- comparison with networks from Riaz et al. (2025)

## Repository structure
|-DataProcessing/
|-WGCNA/
|-GOEnrichmentAnalysis
|-NetworkComparison/
Each folder contains R scripts and README files describing the specific analyses.

## Required R packages 
The following R packages are required to run the analyses:
- WGCNA
- tidyverse
- dplyr
- stringr
- magrittr
- ggplot2
- readxl
- readr
- rtracklayer
- ape
- patchwork
- gridExtra
- flashClust
- pheatmap
- cowplot
- clusterProfiler
- ggalluvial
- simplifyEnrichment
- ggh4x
- ggforce
- reshape2
- igraph


## Data availability
Due to Github file size limitations, some large datasets are not included in this repository.
Links to download those files are offered in the README files within each folder.


